    public class ApplySubgraph<G extends GraphHead,V extends Vertex,E extends Edge,LG extends BaseGraph<G,V,E,LG,GC>,GC extends BaseGraphCollection<G,V,E,LG,GC>>
extends Subgraph<G,V,E,LG,GC>
implements ApplicableUnaryBaseGraphToBaseGraphOperator<GC>
    Extracts a subgraph from each base graph in a graph collection using the given filter functions. The graph head stays unchanged for the subgraph.

    The operator is able to:

    1. extract vertex-induced subgraph
    2. extract edge-induced subgraph via join + union strategy
    3. extract edge-induced subgraph via project + union + join strategy
    4. extract subgraph based on vertex and edge filter function without verification (no joins, use Verify to verify the subgraph)

    • Constructor Detail

      • ApplySubgraph

        public ApplySubgraph(org.apache.flink.api.common.functions.FilterFunction<V> vertexFilterFunction,
                     org.apache.flink.api.common.functions.FilterFunction<E> edgeFilterFunction,
                     Subgraph.Strategy strategy)
        Creates a new sub graph operator instance.

        If both parameters are not null, the operator returns the subgraph defined by filtered vertices and edges.

        If the edgeFilterFunction is null, the operator returns the vertex-induced subgraph.

        If the vertexFilterFunction is null, the operator returns the edge-induced subgraph.

        Parameters:
        vertexFilterFunction - vertex filter function
        edgeFilterFunction - edge filter function
        strategy - sets the execution strategy for the operator
